      "tool": "binskim",
      "ruleId": "BA2014",
      "createdDate": "2026-06-09 00:00:00Z",
      "justification": "BinSkim BA2014 fires on three compiler-generated 'default constructor closure' thunks (??_F...) in upstream V8 -- v8::platform::DefaultPlatform, v8::CpuProfilingOptions, and v8::SnapshotCreator -- emitted into the vendored V8 static libs v8_base_without_compiler.lib / v8_libplatform.lib. These thunks carry no stack buffers, so /GS inserts no cookie and there is nothing for the stack protector to guard; BinSkim reports them as having stack protection disabled, but this is a false positive, not disabled protection in v8-jsi code. The symbols are produced by V8's own compilation (not by src/v8jsi.gyp), so v8-jsi cannot annotate or reflag them without patching vendored V8; /sdl applied to V8 did not clear them and would impose an engine-wide performance cost. Accepted as a residual finding. The genuinely-actionable BinSkim rules (CFG/BA2008, ASLR/BA2009, NX/BA2016, Spectre/BA2024, secure source hashing/BA2004) are enabled and pass via src/v8jsi_settings.gypi."
    }
  }
}
